		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 1:30 AM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=11&mid=9665470391340&num=9&post=1&replyto=96657660914585"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=96657660914585></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=475"><span id=>Artannis</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>5 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.67]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Once you start off, you get two spells and a puny weapon.&nbsp;&nbsp;Memorize those spells and click on them once they are in your spell book.  Then a little gem appears with your mouse pointer.  Move it across to one of the empty gem slots on the side and click.  Note: This is the only way to cast spells.  If you have any online friends, ask them to lend you some money to purchase the rest of your spells.  If not, it's just a simple matter of selling the loot from the corpses of the things you kill.  Cast the Minor Shield spell.  Don't worry the spells outlined in yellow can only be cast on yourself so you don't waste mana on others.  (No I'm not a bastard, but later on you'll find out how much you'll come to appreciate your mana and not waste it.) Now, begin to battle the low-level monsters outside of your city.   Make sure to stay in an area where you can run to the guards if you get in trouble.  Cast the spell from a bit of a distance from your target, then press the auto attack button.  Which is default set to (A).  You really want to change this because when you talk to people you could have accidents.  Especially with guard NPCs, all of which at this point would be able to kill you effortlessly.  I recommend changing it to (0) on the number pad on the right of your keyboard.  Try to keep casting the spell while the battle's going.  If you win, loot the corpse.  Then rest.  Sit down when resting to gather more mana and regenerate your hit points faster.  If you get in trouble, run back to the guards, and always rest by the guards.  This is a basis for your low levels, from 1-5 or so.  During that time, you will get a skill called meditate.  It will be your best friend.  When you sit down to gain mana, go into your spell book and click on the now touchable, meditate button.  This will enable you to gather mana much faster.  Also, practice as many of your skills as you can, while you level, it's very important to keep up with them so that you don't lose tracks.  Save the bonus five points that you get to train with from your guild master, and level up to five on skills like tailoring, alcohol brewing, and what not, just so that it makes it easier when you really carry them out (which levels them most of the time.)  Once you get to 5, you should go to into the wilds and start killing things there.  And don't forget to keep buying your spells.  For a while you get new spells at every four levels or so.    After you start to get weakened from killing things, go meditate near the guards, and try to avoid meditating in the middle of a monster filled zone when you're at such a low level.  As you level up more, you will start to venture father out from you're home city.  That's a good thing so that you can find new challenges, and level up easier.  Try to find new weapons too.  Put some points into the one-hand blunt weapons skill, and begin to work with that.  One hand blunt is in general, the best weapon skill for wizards.  This way, you can hold a magical item in the other hand.  When you get money, and you have to choose between a new spell and equipment, go for the spell.  It can do you a world of good.<br>Keep selling useless things you pick up off of corpses.  It gives more room, and you lose carrying weight.  Next, I recommend checking out Allakazam's Quest Database.  It's an awesome resource and very precise.  Check the quests that are in your area, and see if there's anything that it looks like you can handle.  Once you get to 12.  Get your bind spell and head to Erud's Crossing.  (Make sure you have a magical weapon, or else you can't hit the wisps!)  Erud's crossing features an island in between the continents of Odus and Antonica.  The boats that ferry in between the two continents will take you there.  Don't worry about swimming to the island. The boat docks there.  There you will find an island full of friendly cat like people.  You can purchase water and food at one of the shops.  But whatever you do, DO NOT KILL THE KERRA BEETLES!!!<br>There are two bad things that happen if you do.  One, the cat people get pissed and attack you, and two, an aggravated Fire Elemental spawns.  Do not encounter him yet!  For now, you're best off with the Kerra snakes, and on occasion, spiders.  The bad thing with the spiders is that they attack in-groups.  I wouldn't recommend soloing a wisp till you get to 14.  And make sure that there aren't others near.  They like to help.  Ahhhh!  This is long!  Well, that's how to get to 16.  I'll submit another one of these for leveling from there.  Bye.<br><br>Artannis<br>High Elven<br>Wizard<br>Tunare Server<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>"People will belive any lie either because they want it to be true, or they're arfaid it's true."<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
